      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to go past VORONYA (2). Progressive type who had first try for new yard and this area with a demolition of a few of these last time. Can only be improved for the first try here and although meeting them worse at weights looks the one to beat again. OUR SQUAMOSA (3)  is racing well placing fresh then finishing third behind VORONYA latest. Meets the winner 3kg better and can finish much closer. STANDARD STREET (5) was another from the same race, finishing forth and beaten 11 lengths. Much better off at the weights and can sneak into the finish this time. BEACHBARBECKONS (1) made debut this area for the new yard over a mile in open class. Safely held but better for the experience and well back in grade. Can improve sharply. BRASH LASS (6) has been freshened since finished at the tail in Darwin. Joins new yard and first run here. Worth keeping safe.",
